**Your Job Title:** 
 Manufacturing Engineer Electronics




**Job Location:** 
 Sweden - Danderyd (on-site)




****Purpose:****
 As a Manufacturing Engineer Electronics, you will play a crucial role in supporting our production lines and technicians. You will be responsible for ESD management, component fault analysis and repair, and overseeing the test run process. Your expertise will be vital in maintaining high standards of quality and efficiency in our production of electro-optical measurement systems for surveying, construction, and civil engineering. Your extensive knowledge and experience within electronics will be crucial in this role.




**Key Responsibilities**
* Provide technical support to production to ensure delivery reliability;
* Analyze and address deviations in products and equipment;
* Monitor and improve ergonomics in production;
* Drive process improvements and implement enhanced working methods;
* Identify, develop and plan preventive activities;
* Statistically monitor, measure, and analyze process quality;
* Maintain and calibrate production equipment;
* Maintain and update calibration and work instructions;
* Introduce change order processes and test series in production;
* Ensure quality information is disseminated to relevant managers;
* Participate in production and equipment reviews during the development process;
* Educate production personnel on equipment and methods;
* Analyze and resolve Defect Product Returns (DPRs);
* Support other departments with tests and investigations;
* Lead projects related to production equipment development.


**Competence Requirements**
* Extensive expertise in electronics, complemented by broad competence in areas such as mechanics, optics, production technology, project management, or quality work;
* Proficiency in MS Office and Google programs;
* Excellent knowledge of Swedish and English;
* Strong communication skills;
* Experience from CAD programs is an advantage.


****Why Join Us?****
 At Trimble Inc. we value innovation, collaboration, and continuous improvement. You will have the opportunity to work on exciting projects, lead initiatives, and contribute to the success of our production processes. We offer a supportive work environment, professional development opportunities, and a chance to make a real impact.




 Join us and be a part of our journey towards excellence in manufacturing!




**About Trimble**
 Dedicated to the world’s tomorrow, Trimble is a technology company delivering solutions that enable our customers to work in new ways to measure, build, grow and move goods for a better quality of life. Core technologies in positioning, modelling, connectivity and data analytics connect the digital and physical worlds to improve productivity, quality, safety, transparency and sustainability. From purpose-built products and enterprise lifecycle solutions to industry cloud services, Trimble is transforming critical industries such as construction, geospatial, agriculture and transportation to power an interconnected world of work. For more information about Trimble (NASDAQ: TRMB), visit:
 **www.trimble.com**
**Trimble’s Inclusiveness Commitment**
 We believe in celebrating our differences. That is why our diversity is our strength. To us, that means actively participating in opportunities to be inclusive. Diversity, Equity, and Inclusion have guided our current success while also moving our desire to improve. We actively seek to add members to our community who represent our customers and the places we live and work.




 We have programs in place to make sure our people are seen, heard, and welcomed and most importantly that they know they belong, no matter who they are or where they are coming from.




